new_model

  • new_model(options: ModelOptions, serialized_state?: any): Promise<any>
    • Defined in manager-base.ts:271

    Create and return a promise for a new widget model

    Minimally, one must provide the model_name and widget_class parameters to create a model from Javascript.

    example

    widget_manager.new_model({ model_name: 'WidgetModel', widget_class: 'Jupyter.IntSlider' }) .then((model) => { console.log('Create success!', model); }, (err) => {console.error(err)});

    Parameters

    • options: ModelOptions

      the options for creating the model.

    • Default value serialized_state: any = {}

      attribute values for the model.

    Returns Promise<any>
